  "body": "### Description\nWhen selecting the starting point for a state regeneration, if the epoch boundary state is only a few slots better than a state available from the store or another task, we should prefer the already in-memory states as starting points rather than loading the epoch boundary state.\n\nA reasonable threshold is likely to be the number of slots between epoch boundary states.",
